abstract: Apple beat Wall Street expectations with its earnings report, but shares of its stock fell more than 11 percent in after-hours trading as investors fretted over its future.

lead_paragraph: Apple beat Wall Street expectations with its earnings report Tuesday, but its shares fell more than 11 percent in after-hours trading as investors fretted over its prospects.

headline.main: Apple Earnings Up, but Stock Falls on Outlook
headline.print_headline: Apple Beats Forecast, but Shares Tumble Anyway
